**THEMES** — @HyperliquidX is laser-focused on Hyperliquid's core product: perpetual futures trading on their high-performance L1 blockchain. Posts hammer trading volumes, open interest, new perp listings (BTC/ETH), zero-gas execution, and onchain order book superiority over CEXs. Secondary beats include token airdrops (HYPE), yield vaults for USDC, and stats dashboards. No fluff on general crypto news, NFTs, or memes—pure product updates, tech deep-dives, and growth metrics over the past month, signaling a mature exchange pushing TVL and user adoption.

**FORMATS** — Predominantly single tweets for stats blasts and announcements (70%), threads for technical explanations (20%, always numbered 1/N), quote-RTs of user wins or partners (10%). Zero standalone replies or pure retweets; everything original or amplified content. Concise, punchy style: stat → hook → CTA, optimized for quick scrolls.

**VISUAL VOCABULARY** — Dark mode supremacy: black/navy backgrounds, neon green/red accents for buy/sell/price action, Hyperliquid purple (#8B5CF6) for logos/text. Charts are minimalist line/bar with glowing lines; videos use particle explosions (green/red sparks for trades), fast zooms on code/orderbooks, 20-45s loops with bass-heavy sound design. Recurring: trading UI screenshots (clean, terminal-like), yield graphs pulsing upward, branded gifs with 'Deposit/Trade Now' overlays. No photos, stock images, or casual visuals— all custom motion graphics evoking speed/tech precision.

**WHAT'S NOTABLE** — Recurring discipline: daily/near-daily volume/OI stats posts as 'launch artifact' for retention (e.g., 'Hyperliquid Stats' template with exact metrics). Meme template potential in particle explosion vids (adaptable for Infinex wallet launches: green sparks for deposits). Jumps out: thread format as 'tech evangelist' discipline, always 4-5 parts ending in 'Build on Hyperliquid'—copy for Infinex onchain wallet flows. No engagement bait; impressions driven by product velocity.

